      "date": "2013-03-07 16:19:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (3 inline comments)\n\nIt seems many other rpc calls ptlrpc_queue_wait() without any limit. In fact only ldlm client calls mdc_enter_request().\n Should we extent the limit to all RPC?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cc420685bb783f069923e6bcaf16f73f04d0123b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-07 16:57:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> It seems many other rpc calls ptlrpc_queue_wait() without any limit. In fact only ldlm client calls mdc_enter_request().\nShould we extent the limit to all RPC?\n\nIndeed, this was one reason for my disagreeableness on the Jira ticket. If these RPCs are not especially expensive then why are they counted while others aren't. Furthermore why not use just one counter?",
